            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGod's%20kindness%20leads%20to%20repentance.%20We%20once%20were%20lost%2C%20irretrievable%20sinners%2C%20but%20when%20we%20realize%20that%20God%20still%20loves%20us%20enough%20to%20forgive%20us%20in%20Christ%2C%20it%20will%20break%20our%20wills%20and%20cause%20us%20to%20cry%20out%20to%20Him%20for%20mercy.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDavid%20was%20so%20overwhelmed%20by%20God's%20kindness%20in%20promising%20to%20bless%20his%20future%20household%20that%20he%20exclaimed%2C%20%22Who%20am%20I%2C%20O%20Lord%20God%2C%20and%20what%20is%20my%20family%2C%20that%20you%20have%20brought%20me%20this%20far%3F%20And%20now%2C%20O%20God%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20everything%20else%2C%20you%20speak%20of%20giving%20me%20a%20lasting%20dynasty!%20You%20speak%20as%20though%20I%20were%20someone%20very%20great%2C%20O%20Lord%20God%22%20(1%20Chronicles%2017%3A16-17).%20Such%20honor%20and%20kindness%20from%20God%20made%20David%20a%20humble%2C%20not%20proud%2C%20man.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20demolished%20the%20idea%20that%20God's%20goodness%20grants%20a%20person%20self-righteousness.%20The%20Jews%20he%20so%20often%20preached%20to%20felt%20this%20way%20when%20comparing%20themselves%20to%20the%20Gentiles%20(Romans%202).%20We%20must%20never%20fail%20to%20remember%20that%20we%20are%20no%20better%20than%20anyone%20else%2C%20and%20if%20not%20for%20the%20kindness%20of%20God%2C%20we%20would%20be%20just%20like%20everyone%20else!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBe%20humbled%20today%20over%20the%20fact%20that%2C%20in%20His%20kindness%2C%20God%20has%20forgiven%20you.%20Never%20let%20that%20forgiveness%20be%20perverted%20into%20an%20attitude%20of%20superiority.%20Stay%20repentant%20and%20ever%20grateful%20that%20He%20has%20transformed%20your%20life.%20This%20continual%20gratitude%20and%20repentance%20will%20keep%20you%20from%20pride%20and%20religious%20arrogance%20from%20now%20until%20you%20see%20Him%20face-to-face!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
